Western immunoblot analysis of LC3B revealed decreased LC3B I and increased LC3B II protein levels in virus-infected cells compared to mock, providing evidence of autophagy activation and/or block during IAV infection of either avian or human cells (

  Fig 4A, 4E and 4F; 
  5A, 
  5E and 5F
 ). In avian DF-1 cells, levels of LC3B I were slightly decreased and levels of LC3B II were slightly increased over mock, but LC3B I and LC3B II levels were generally comparable among human M- and avian M-containing viruses (

  Fig 4E and 4F
 ). Importantly, human A549 cells infected with PR8 avian M-containing viruses consistently showed lower levels of LC3B I, and higher levels of LC3B II than A549 cells infected with PR8 NL09 M as well as other human M-containing viruses (

  Fig 5E and 5F).
